<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075409>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Colours in life of Tuerkayana rotundum (Quoy & Gaimard, 1824). A, male (47.8 × 37.8 mm) (ZRC 2008.506), Panglao Philippines; B, male (37.6 × 29.0 mm) (ZRC 2012.103), Vanuatu; C, male (37.0 × 28.4 mm) (ZRC 2012.103), Vanuatu; D, male, New Caledonia (specimen not collected); E, male (57.6 × 44.5 mm) (ZRC 2013.1074), North Keeling Island, Cocos-Keeling Islands; F, male, Blowholes, Christmas Island (specimen not collected)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075409/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075411>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Overall views of Tuerkayana rotundum (Quoy & Gaimard, 1824). A, male (50.2 × 38.6 mm) (ZRC 2000.566), Guam; B, male (53.3 × 41.0 mm) (ZRC 1998.474), Taiwan; C, male (47.8 × 37.8 mm) (ZRC 2008.506), Philippines; D, female (38.3 × 29.5 mm) (MNHN-IU-2013-13174), Wallis & Futuna Islands; E, male (57.6 × 44.5 mm) (ZRC 2013.1074), Cocos-Keeling Islands; F, female (holotype of Discoplax pagenstecheri Kossmann, 1878) (55.1 × 44.1 mm) (SMF 6872), Australian Seas; G, H, male (no measurements) (Mauritius Institute), Mauritius." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075411/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075421>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Dorsal views of carapaces of Tuerkayana rotundum. A, male (50.2 × 38.6 mm) (ZRC 2000.566), Guam; B, male (53.3 × 41.0 mm) (ZRC 1998.474), Taiwan; C, male (47.8 × 37.8 mm) (ZRC 2008.506), Philippines; D, female (38.3 × 29.5 mm) (MNHN-IU-2013-13174), Wallis & Futuna Islands; E, male (57.6 × 44.5 mm) (ZRC 2013.1074), Cocos-Keeling Islands; F, female (holotype of Discoplax pagenstecheri Kossmann, 1878) (55.1 × 44.1 mm) (SMF 6872), Australian Seas." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075421/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075423>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Frontal views of carapaces of Tuerkayana rotundum (Quoy & Gaimard, 1824).A, male (50.2 × 38.6 mm) (ZRC 2000.566), Guam; B, male (53.3 × 41.0 mm) (ZRC 1998.474), Taiwan; C, male (47.8 × 37.8 mm) (ZRC 2008.506), Philippines; D, female (38.3 × 29.5 mm) (MNHN-IU-2013-13174), Wallis & Futuna Islands; E, male (57.6 × 44.5 mm) (ZRC 2013.1074), Cocos-Keeling Islands; F, female (holotype of Discoplax pagenstecheri Kossmann, 1878) (55.1 × 44.1 mm) (SMF 6872), Australian Seas." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075423/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075425>
    dc:description "Fig. 7. Third maxillipeds and carapaces of Tuerkayana species. A, T. rotundum, male (50.2 × 38.6 mm) (ZRC 2000.566), Guam; B, T. rotundum, male (47.8 × 37.8 mm) (ZRC 2008.506), Philippines; C, D, T. latens n. sp., holotype male (52.8 × 42.7 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-5594), French Polynesia. A, left third maxilliped; C, right third maxilliped; B, D, lateral views of carapaces." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075425/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075427>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Thoracic sternums, male pleons and chelae of Tuerkayana species. A, T. rotundum, male (50.2 × 38.6 mm) (ZRC 2000.566), Guam; B, T. rotundum, male (53.3 × 41.0 mm) (ZRC 1998.474), Taiwan; C, T. rotundum, male (57.6 × 44.5 mm) (ZRC 2013.1074), Cocos-Keeling Islands; D, T. rotundum, male (42.9 × 34.3 mm) (UF 6316), Tuvalu; E, T. rotundum n. sp., male (51.7 × 41.6 mm) (UF 2192), Niue; F, T. latens n. sp., holotype male (52.8 × 42.7 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-5594), French Polynesia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075427/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075429>
    dc:description "Fig. 9. Outer views of chelae of Tuerkayana species. A, T. rotundum, male (50.2 × 38.6 mm) (ZRC 2000.566), Guam; B, T. rotundum, male (53.3 × 41.0 mm) (ZRC 1998.474), Taiwan; C, T. rotundum, male (57.6 × 44.5 mm) (ZRC 2013.1074), Cocos-Keeling Islands; D, T. latens n. sp., holotype male (52.8 × 42.7 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-5594), French Polynesia. A–C, right chelae; D, left chela." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075429/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075431>
    dc:description "Fig. 10. Third and fourth ambulatory legs of Tuerkayana species. A, E, T. rotundum, male (50.2 × 38.6 mm) (ZRC 2000.566), Guam; B, F, T. rotundum, male (53.3 × 41.0 mm) (ZRC 1998.474), Taiwan; C, G, T. rotundum, male (57.6 × 44.5 mm) (ZRC 2013.1074), Cocos-Keeling Islands; D, H, T. latens n. sp., holotype male (52.8 × 42.7 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-5594), French Polynesia. A–D, right third ambulatory legs; E–H, right fourth ambulatory legs." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075431/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075433>
    dc:description "Fig. 11. Left G1s (denuded) of Tuerkayana species. A, E, I, T. rotundum, male (50.2 × 38.6 mm) (ZRC 2000.566), Guam; B, F, J, T. rotundum, male (53.3 × 41.0 mm) (ZRC 1998.474), Taiwan; C, G, K, T. rotundum, male (57.6 × 44.5 mm) (ZRC 2013.1074), Cocos-Keeling Islands; D, H, L, T. latens n. sp., holotype male (52.8 × 42.7 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-5594), French Polynesia. A–D, ventral views; E–H, dorsal views; I–L, dorsomesial views. Scales: A–D = 5.0 mm; E–L = 2.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075433/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8075437>
    dc:description "Fig. 13. Collection sites for Tuerkayana rotundum (Quoy & Gaimard, 1824) (blue squares) and T. latens n. sp. (red squares) used in this study (Table 1). Empty blue and red squares mean the additional records of the two species from other references (e.g., Türkay 1974a; Innocenti and Vannini 2007; Ng and Shih 2014). Different lines indicate the updated ranges of the two species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8075437/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

